data.title: AI-powered mobile clinics in rural India improve breast cancer screening. NVIDIA & MedCognetics partner to provide healthcare to underserved areas.
data.description: NVIDIA has partnered with MedCognetics to provide AI-enhanced breast cancer screenings through mobile clinics, aiming to offer vital healthcare services to underserved regions in India. This collaboration combines NVIDIA's advanced technology with MedCognetics' medical expertise to improve early detection rates. The initiative is set to reach a significant number of individuals in need, potentially saving lives by diagnosing breast cancer at earlier stages.

data.title: Trust Stamp to exchange warrants with institutional investor, likely generating $4.3 million before expenses.
data.description: Trust Stamp, a global provider of AI-powered identity services, has reached a warrant inducement agreement with an institutional investor for the exercise of outstanding warrants issued in September 2024, December 2024, and January 2025. The investor will exercise warrants to purchase 413,696 shares at $4.83 per share from September 2024 and 621,303 shares at $8.45 per share from January 2025 after the exercise prices were reduced to $4.20 per share. Additionally, all outstanding December 2024 warrants will be exchanged for new warrants. The total gross proceeds from the exercise of warrants are projected to be around $4.3 million before placement agent fees and offering expenses are deducted.

data.title: Bitcoin's 17th anniversary sees BTC bouncing to $109,000, up from a $207,000 market cap in 2010 to almost $2 trillion.
data.description: On the 17th anniversary of the Bitcoin White Paper, the price of Bitcoin (CRYPTO: BTC) soared to $109,000. Originally created by Satoshi Nakamoto, Bitcoin started with a market cap of $207,000 in 2010 and has now reached nearly $2 trillion. Despite hitting a record high of $126,000, the price has since retreated as some investors view the dip as a buying opportunity. The current sentiment towards Bitcoin has turned cautious as it consolidates its position. Jeff Park, an advisor at Bitwise, shared insights on the market trends.
